abstract: Assailants attacked several protest camps in north and south Lebanon early on Tuesday, according to state-run media, demolishing tents and burning down others as anger boiled over in the capital following a video deemed offensive to the country’s Shiites.
snippet: Assailants attacked several protest camps in north and south Lebanon early on Tuesday, according to state-run media, demolishing tents and burning down others as anger boiled over in the capital following a video deemed offensive to the country’s ...
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Assailants attacked several protest camps in north and south Lebanon early on Tuesday, according to state-run media, demolishing tents and burning down others as anger boiled over in the capital following a video deemed offensive to the country’s Shiites.
headline_main: Assailants Attack Several Protest Camps Across Lebanon
headline_print_headline: Assailants Attack Several Protest Camps Across Lebanon

abstract: Mart Helme, the Estonian interior minister, insulted Prime Minister Sanna Marin and claimed that Finland was led by “Reds” bent on destroying the country.
snippet: Mart Helme, the Estonian interior minister, insulted Prime Minister Sanna Marin and claimed that Finland was led by “Reds” bent on destroying the country.
lead_paragraph: Estonia’s leaders have apologized after the country’s interior minister called the new prime minister of neighboring Finland, Sanna Marin, “a sales girl.”

abstract: The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
snippet: The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
headline_main: Exclusive: U.S. Finalizing Rules to Limit Sensitive Tech Exports to China, Others
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: U.S. Finalizing Rules to Limit Sensitive Tech Exports to China, Others

abstract: Estonia's nationalist interior minister narrowly survived a no-confidence vote Tuesday that was triggered by his mocking of neighboring Finland's young new prime minister and her party.
snippet: Estonia's nationalist interior minister narrowly survived a no-confidence vote Tuesday that was triggered by his mocking of neighboring Finland's young new prime minister and her party.
lead_paragraph: HELSINKI — Estonia's nationalist interior minister narrowly survived a no-confidence vote Tuesday that was triggered by his mocking of neighboring Finland's young new prime minister and her party.
headline_main: Vote to Remove Estonia Minister Over Jab at Finnish PM Fails
headline_print_headline: Vote to Remove Estonia Minister Over Jab at Finnish PM Fails

abstract: The country has been gripped by strikes over President Emmanuel Macron’s plans to overhaul a generous but dizzyingly complex pension system.
snippet: The country has been gripped by strikes over President Emmanuel Macron’s plans to overhaul a generous but dizzyingly complex pension system.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Strikes have disrupted France over the past few weeks, as labor unions angry over President Emmanuel Macron’s planned pension overhauls have ground trains to a halt, kept some schools closed, and taken to the streets to pressure the government.

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote this week on whether to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote this week on whether to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives will vote this week on whether to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
headline_main: Factbox: Abuse of Power, Obstruction-The Charges Against Trump Explained
headline_print_headline: Factbox: Abuse of Power, Obstruction-The Charges Against Trump Explained

abstract: South Sudan's President Salva Kiir and former rebel leader Riek Machar have agreed to form a transitional unity government even if they fail to resolve all their differences before a new deadline, the two leaders said on Tuesday.
snippet: South Sudan's President Salva Kiir and former rebel leader Riek Machar have agreed to form a transitional unity government even if they fail to resolve all their differences before a new deadline, the two leaders said on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: JUBA — South Sudan's President Salva Kiir and former rebel leader Riek Machar have agreed to form a transitional unity government even if they fail to resolve all their differences before a new deadline, the two leaders said on Tuesday.
headline_main: South Sudan's Kiir and Machar Say They Will Form Government
headline_print_headline: South Sudan's Kiir and Machar Say They Will Form Government
